sql:
SELECT AVG(feedback_score) AS average_feedback_score
FROM consumer_feedback
WHERE market_id = 0;

SELECT mean_score
FROM factors
WHERE factor_id = 1;

SELECT market_id, AVG(feedback_score) AS average_score
FROM consumer_feedback
GROUP BY market_id;

external_knowledge:
market_id refers to a specific market where the feedback was collected; 
feedback_score refers to the score given by the consumer for the attribute; 
feedback_comments refer to the text comments provided by the consumer; 
A market with id 1 is considered the main or primary market.

sql:
SELECT factor_name, mean_score
FROM factors
ORDER BY mean_score DESC;
